(secondQuint)Ultrasound Evaluation of the Rotator Cable and Associated Structures.

.

 The purpose of this study is to document normal and abnormal appearances of various shoulder structures (rotator cable and rotator cuff).

 This study will recruit healthy volunteers and patients who have been referred to Radiology for a symptomatic shoulder (a shoulder that is causing the patient pain, or is limited in its ability to move.

) Both groups will undergo ultrasound imaging of the shoulder.

